<p>Martins would modify anything for decorative purposes, and this belt was no exception. It&rsquo;s unclear whether she wore it, but she hung it on the wall to attract light with its golden glint. This &ldquo;magpie instinct for glitter and shiny objects&rdquo; (Emslie, 1997:72) is evident throughout the Owl House.</p>
<p>Her love for beautiful things was well known, and in her youth Martins was a fashionable dresser. &ldquo;Many of her clothes, in later years, came from her sister, Alida, who understood that Helen was short of cash. Alida traveled abroad and sometimes brought back exotic items for Helen&rdquo; (Graaff, personal communication 2017, 27 October).</p>